message.content:
I need to identify the specific line items and values related to interest accrued but not yet received (interest receivable) from the financial statements.

Looking at the balance sheet, I can see an account specifically labeled "Interest Receivable":
- Initial amount (2023-12-31): 0.00
- End amount (2024-02-05): 14575.80

This is confirmed by the cash flow statement which shows "(Increase) Decrease in Interest Receivable" of -14575.80, indicating an increase in interest receivable.

Further validation comes from the income statement, which shows "Interest Income" of 14575.80, matching the end value of Interest Receivable.

This makes sense as Interest Receivable represents interest income that has been earned but not yet received in cash, which is exactly what the task is asking for - interest accrued but not yet received.

{"solution": {'initial value': '0.00', 'end value': '14575.80'}}
